body.p:
Start PB: Exert start with a high signal.
Bring signal H (OK) if wiring is good, and button is pressed,
as long as there is not an eStop Cmd

Pendant Enable
Set Allow Pendant Moves if pendant mode is rx from PLC and enable sw is made.
Make a pulse on a momentary press, or continuous if button is held in.

No module check for pendant emo becuase it goes into the safe controller, and
there is no separate module check.

No module check for pendant enable becuase it goes into the safe controller, and
there is no separate module check.

Stop PB: H: Allow to Run, L: Stop
Bring signal H (OK) if wiring is good, and button is not
pressed (both contacts in normal state).

Bring signal L (Stop) if wiring is not okay, or the button is pressed.

Button is wired so a high is pressed, but we want a high to the PLC to be allow
to run.
